node.text:
TSR STAFF: Christina C! @cdelafresh 
________
#TSRTech: Remember when we hoped those futuristic music videos were a window into the future? 
________
Well it’s 2021 and I’m highly disappointed in what these recent years delivered in the name of technology but there’s no denying those videos are works of art. Artists like Missy Elliott and Busta Rhymes were undisputedly ahead of their time with the visuals.
________
While this current era is definitely giving “one star, would not recommend,” let me take y’all back to a simpler time when the best tech existed on our screens.
________
Which of these throwback music videos with tech-inspired themes were your favorite? Let us know!

#TSRCutTheFoolery: A Russian woman is reportedly suing McDonald’s over one of the companies ads that featured cheeseburgers and chicken nuggets, claiming the tempting ad caused her to break her fast during Lent.
________
Ksenia Ovchinnikova, who identifies as an Orthodox Christian, said she gave up meat and other animal products for the six weeks of lent in 2019, @Insider reports.
________
The case was first reported by Russian state media and picked up by western outlets including Fox News, which wrote that the woman abstained from eating meat for a month when the “enticing” McDonald's ad made her give in, according to her lawsuit.
______
